## Coding Standards

- Use existing project conventions (linter, formatter, naming).
- No secrets in source code — use environment variables.
- All public APIs must have documentation or types.
- Error handling: fail fast with clean messages. No raw tracebacks at CLI boundaries.
- Every CLI command must have a catch-all exception handler producing clean error + exit 1.

## Verification Standards

- All tasks require independent verification before greenlight.
- Integration tests must exercise every pipeline step they claim to cover.
- CLI commands must be tested at the subprocess level, not just unit-tested.
- See `.spectra/guardrails.md` for learned Signs from past failures.

